<!-- ══════ ACTION 1 ══════ -->
<h1>Action 1 — Add BREVO_API_KEY to Netlify</h1>
<hr class="rule">
<span class="blocker">⚠ Critical blocker</span>
<p style="margin-top:8pt">Until this is done, every form submission on the live site will silently fail to reach Brevo. The serverless function is deployed and ready — it is only missing the key.</p>

<div class="warn"><strong>Who:</strong> Whoever has admin access to the Netlify account for meridianhealth.com.au</div>

<h2>Step-by-step</h2>

<div class="step-block">
  <div class="step-num">1</div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <h3>Get your Brevo API key</h3>
    <p>Log into Brevo → click your name/avatar (top right) → <strong>SMTP &amp; API</strong> → <strong>API Keys</strong> tab → <strong>Generate a new API key</strong> → name it "Meridian Netlify" → copy the key immediately (it is only shown once).</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step-block">
  <div class="step-num">2</div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <h3>Open Netlify environment variables</h3>
    <p>Log into Netlify → select the <strong>meridianhealth.com.au</strong> site → <strong>Site configuration</strong> (left sidebar) → <strong>Environment variables</strong> → <strong>Add a variable</strong>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step-block">
  <div class="step-num">3</div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <h3>Add the variable</h3>
    <p>Key: <span class="path">BREVO_API_KEY</span><br>
    Value: paste the key copied from Brevo<br>
    Scope: All scopes (or at minimum: Functions)</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step-block">
  <div class="step-num">4</div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <h3>Trigger a redeploy</h3>
    <p>Netlify → <strong>Deploys</strong> tab → <strong>Trigger deploy → Deploy site</strong>. The function will pick up the new variable. Takes ~60 seconds.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step-block">
  <div class="step-num">5</div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <h3>Test it</h3>
    <p>Submit the enquiry form on the live site with a test email address. Check Brevo → Contacts — the contact should appear within 30 seconds with <span class="path">enquiry_submitted_date</span> and the correct pathway tag.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ══════ ACTION 2 ══════ -->
<h1>Action 2 — Set up Brevo contact attributes and tags</h1>
<hr class="rule">
<div class="note"><strong>Who:</strong> Brevo account admin &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Reference:</strong> <span class="path">brevo-automation-flow.doc</span> Section C &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> ~30 min</div>

<p>This only needs to be done once. These attributes and tags are used by every automation to segment and personalise communications.</p>

<h2>Contact attributes to create</h2>
<p>Brevo → Contacts → <strong>Settings</strong> (top right gear) → <strong>Contact attributes</strong> → <strong>Add a new attribute</strong>.</p>
<p>Create all seven in the <strong>Normal attributes</strong> section:</p>

<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Attribute name (exact)</th><th>Type</th><th>Used for</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">enquiry_submitted_date</span></td><td>Date</td><td>Automation entry trigger timing</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">appointment_datetime</span></td><td>Date</td><td>72-hr reminder date-based trigger</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">consultation_booked</span></td><td>Boolean</td><td>Exit condition for enquiry nurture</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">consultation_completed</span></td><td>Boolean</td><td>Entry condition for post-consultation</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">ENQUIRY_PATHWAY</span></td><td>Text</td><td>Stores pathway from form (bariatric / upper-gi / metabolic)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">ENQUIRY_MESSAGE</span></td><td>Text</td><td>Stores patient's free-text message</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">clinician</span></td><td>Text</td><td>Personalise emails with treating clinician name</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="note">Brevo note: <span class="path">FIRSTNAME</span> and <span class="path">LASTNAME</span> are built-in — do not recreate them.</div>

<h2>Tags to create</h2>
<p>Brevo → Contacts → <strong>Tags</strong> → <strong>Create tag</strong>. Create all nine:</p>

<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Tag name (exact)</th><th>Applied when</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">enquiry_bariatric</span></td><td>Form submitted with pathway = bariatric</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">enquiry_uppergi</span></td><td>Form submitted with pathway = upper-gi</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">enquiry_metabolic</span></td><td>Form submitted with pathway = metabolic</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">booked_consult</span></td><td>Consultation booked (set manually by admin or via booking system)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">consult_completed</span></td><td>Consultation completed</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">face_to_face</span></td><td>In-person appointment — triggers clinic address block in emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">telehealth</span></td><td>Telehealth appointment — triggers Coviu link block in emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">pathway_surgical</span></td><td>Confirmed surgical pathway</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">pathway_metabolic</span></td><td>Confirmed metabolic/GLP-1 pathway</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ══════ ACTION 3 ══════ -->
<h1>Action 3 — Build email templates in Brevo</h1>
<hr class="rule">
<div class="note"><strong>Who:</strong> Brevo account admin &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Reference:</strong> Copy docs listed below &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> ~90 min for all templates</div>

<p>Brevo → <strong>Email campaigns</strong> → <strong>Templates</strong> → <strong>New template</strong>.</p>
<p>Use the <strong>Drag &amp; drop editor</strong> or paste the copy into a simple text/HTML template. All copy is verbatim and paste-ready from the reference docs.</p>

<h2>Templates to create (in order)</h2>

<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Template name</th><th>Subject line</th><th>Copy source</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 01 Enquiry Received</span></td><td>Meridian Health — We've received your enquiry</td><td><span class="path">brevo-automation-flow.doc</span> Stage 01</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 02 Appointment Confirmed</span></td><td>Your Meridian consultation is confirmed</td><td><span class="path">brevo-automation-flow.doc</span> Stage 06</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 03 Re-Engagement</span></td><td>Still thinking things through?</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Email 03</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 04 Consultation Overview</span></td><td>What to expect at your first Meridian consultation</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Email 04</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 05 Pathway Education</span></td><td>Three pathways. One team.</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Email 05</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 08 Pre-Consultation Reminder</span></td><td>Your Meridian consultation is tomorrow</td><td><span class="path">brevo-stage-08-setup-checklist.html</span> Phase 1</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Email 09 Post-Consultation Next Steps</span></td><td>Your next steps with Meridian</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-09-post-consultation.html</span> Section 2</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10A Sleeve Email 1</span></td><td>Your sleeve gastrectomy — what to expect</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10A</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10A Sleeve Email 2</span></td><td>Preparing well makes a real difference</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10A</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10A Sleeve Email 3</span></td><td>Life after your sleeve gastrectomy</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10A</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10B Bypass Emails 1–3</span></td><td>(see Track 10B in copy doc)</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10B</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10C Upper GI Emails 1–3</span></td><td>(see Track 10C in copy doc)</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10C</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10D GLP-1 Emails 1–3</span></td><td>(see Track 10D in copy doc)</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10D</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="path">MH — Track 10E Revision Emails 1–3</span></td><td>(see Track 10E in copy doc)</td><td><span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span> Track 10E</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Conditional blocks (Emails 02 and 08)</h2>
<p>Emails 02 and 08 each contain two conditional blocks — one for face-to-face patients, one for telehealth. These use Brevo's native conditional syntax. The exact copy and syntax for both are in the reference docs. The key pattern is:</p>
<p style="font-family:monospace;background:#f0ede6;padding:8pt 10pt;font-size:9.5pt">
{% if contact.face_to_face %}<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;[clinic address block]<br>
{% elsif contact.telehealth %}<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;[Coviu link block]<br>
{% endif %}
</p>
<div class="warn"><strong>Address block confirmed:</strong> The face-to-face address block in Email 02 and Email 08 uses <strong>Suite 8, Level 8, Brenan Place, Victoria Parade, Fitzroy VIC 3065</strong> — confirmed by the practice manager on 26 May 2026. Both templates have been updated.</div>

<!-- ══════ ACTION 4 ══════ -->
<h1>Action 4 — Build and activate the automations in Brevo</h1>
<hr class="rule">
<div class="note"><strong>Who:</strong> Brevo account admin &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Reference:</strong> <span class="path">brevo-automation-flow.doc</span> Section B &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> ~60 min</div>

<p>Brevo → <strong>Automations</strong> → <strong>Create a workflow</strong>. Build five automations. Descriptions to paste into Brevo's internal description field are in Section D of the automation flow doc.</p>

<h2>Automation 1 — Enquiry Nurture</h2>
<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Name</td><td><span class="path">MH — Enquiry Nurture</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Entry trigger</td><td>Event: <span class="path">enquiry_submitted</span> fires (sent by website form)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Exit condition</td><td>Contact has tag <span class="path">booked_consult</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sequence</td><td>Email 01 (immediate) → wait 24 hrs → Email 03 → wait 3 days → Email 04 → wait 2 days → Email 05</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Re-entry</td><td>No</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Automation 2 — Pre-Consultation Reminder</h2>
<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Name</td><td><span class="path">MH — Pre-Consultation Reminder</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Entry trigger</td><td>Date-based: <span class="path">appointment_datetime</span> minus 72 hours; filter: contact has tag <span class="path">booked_consult</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sequence</td><td>Email 08 (immediate on trigger) + SMS 08 in parallel</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Re-entry</td><td>Yes (each new appointment)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Full setup</td><td>See <span class="path">brevo-stage-08-setup-checklist.html</span> Phase 2 for exact Brevo UI steps</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Automation 3 — Appointment Confirmed</h2>
<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Name</td><td><span class="path">MH — Appointment Confirmed</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Entry trigger</td><td>Tag added: <span class="path">booked_consult</span> (set manually by admin when booking is made)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sequence</td><td>Email 02 (immediate) + SMS 07 in parallel</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Re-entry</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Automation 4 — Post-Consultation</h2>
<table class="t">
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Name</td><td><span class="path">MH — Post-Consultation</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Entry trigger</td><td>Tag added: <span class="path">consult_completed</span> (set manually by admin after consultation)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sequence</td><td>Wait 2 hours → Email 09 → wait 7 days → pathway track branch (see below)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Branching</td><td>If tag <span class="path">enquiry_bariatric</span> → Track 10A or 10B; if <span class="path">enquiry_uppergi</span> → Track 10C; if <span class="path">enquiry_metabolic</span> → Track 10D; if revision → Track 10E</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Activation order</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Build all automations in <strong>Draft</strong> mode first</li>
  <li>Complete Action 5 (confirm suite number and clinician sign-off)</li>
  <li>Activate Automation 1 (Enquiry Nurture) first — this is the entry point</li>
  <li>Activate Automations 3 and 4 together</li>
  <li>Activate Automation 2 (Pre-Consultation Reminder) last, after running the 72-hr test below</li>
</ol>

<h2>72-hour test before activating Automation 2</h2>
<p>See <span class="path">brevo-stage-08-setup-checklist.html</span> Phase 3 for the full test procedure. In summary:</p>
<ul class="check">
  <li>Create a test contact in Brevo with <span class="path">booked_consult</span> tag applied</li>
  <li>Set <span class="path">appointment_datetime</span> to exactly 73 hours from now</li>
  <li>Confirm the automation shows the contact as enrolled</li>
  <li>Wait for the trigger (or use a 1-hour test offset to speed up verification)</li>
  <li>Confirm Email 08 arrives with correct conditional block for appointment type</li>
  <li>Confirm SMS 08 fires in parallel</li>
  <li>Record results in the test completion table in the checklist doc</li>
</ul>

<!-- ══════ ACTION 5 ══════ -->
<h1>Action 5 — Confirm suite number and clinician sign-off</h1>
<hr class="rule">
<div class="note"><strong>Who:</strong> Practice admin + clinical team &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> Short — just a check and confirmation</div>

<h2>5a — Confirm suite / level for address block <span style="font-size:9pt;font-weight:normal;color:#27ae60">&#10003; Complete</span></h2>
<p>Two email templates contain a face-to-face address block: <strong>Email 02</strong> (appointment confirmation) and <strong>Email 08</strong> (72-hr reminder).</p>
<p>The confirmed address is:</p>
<div class="note">
  Suite 8, Level 8<br>
  Brenan Place<br>
  Victoria Parade<br>
  Fitzroy VIC 3065<br><br>
  <em>Confirmed by the practice manager on 26 May 2026. Address blocks updated in both Email 02 and Email 08.</em>
</div>
<p>This action is complete. No further changes required for the address block.</p>

<h2>5b — Clinician sign-off on Stage 10 pathway copy</h2>
<p>The 15 emails across the five pathway nurture tracks (Tracks 10A–10E) were written to match Meridian's clinical voice. Before activating, at least one treating clinician should review the copy to confirm:</p>
<ul class="check">
  <li>Track 10A (Sleeve gastrectomy) — 3 emails — reviewed by surgeon</li>
  <li>Track 10B (Gastric bypass) — 3 emails — reviewed by surgeon</li>
  <li>Track 10C (Reflux / Upper GI) — 3 emails — reviewed by surgeon</li>
  <li>Track 10D (GLP-1 / Metabolic medicine) — 3 emails — reviewed by physician</li>
  <li>Track 10E (Revision surgery) — 3 emails — reviewed by surgeon</li>
</ul>
<p>Copy is in: <span class="path">brevo-email-copy.html</span></p>
<p>Any amendments should be made to the Brevo templates before activating the Post-Consultation automation (Automation 4).</p>

<!-- ══════ SUMMARY ══════ -->
<h1>Summary checklist</h1>
<hr class="rule">

<table class="t">
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Action</th><th>Who</th><th>Blocker?</th><th>Done</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>Add <span class="path">BREVO_API_KEY</span> to Netlify environment variables + redeploy</td><td>Netlify admin</td><td style="color:#c0392b;font-weight:700">Yes</td><td>☐</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2a</td><td>Create 7 contact attributes in Brevo</td><td>Brevo admin</td><td>No</td><td>☐</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2b</td><td>Create 9 tags in Brevo</td><td>Brevo admin</td><td>No</td><td>☐</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>Build all 14 email templates in Brevo (paste copy from docs)</td><td>Brevo admin</td><td>No</td><td>☐</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4a</td><td>Build 4 automations in Brevo (Draft mode)</td><td>Brevo admin</td><td>No</td><td>☐</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5a</td><td>Confirm suite number for Email 02 + 08 address block</td><td>Practice admin</td><td>No</td><td style="color:#27ae60;font-weight:700">&#10003;</td></tr>
